On the International Day of the Girl, the United States reaffirms its commitment to empowering girls to pursue their dreams and become leaders. The article highlights the challenges that many girls face, such as limited access to education and employment opportunities, as well as societal mindsets that view girls as burdens. The United States is taking steps to encourage girls to explore STEM fields, expand access to vocational training, and promote girls' rights and self-confidence. The article emphasizes the importance of providing young women with the necessary resources and opportunities to reach their full potential.